This page is a supplementary teaching scaffold for HTML project assembly.

## Core concept

A project builder turns compiled module artefacts and entry link plans into route-level artefacts.

## Beanstalk boundary

The HTML builder owns:

- entry selection
- route and document policy
- activation of one compiled module's dormant root work
- compile-time and runtime fragment interleaving
- mixed JavaScript and Wasm planning
- external runtime glue
- tracked assets
- output records

A module may feed several entry assemblies without recompilation.

The builder does not parse source or trigger deferred AST, HIR, generic or borrow work.

## Rewrite focus

Explain the difference between semantic compilation and artefact assembly, then show why entry activation is a link decision rather than a compiler mode.

Canonical details live in `docs/build-system-design.md`.
